    {
      "title": "The Jussive Mood (المجزوم)",
      "titleArabic": "المجزوم",
      "content": [
        "The jussive (majzūm) is one of three moods of the present tense verb. It is induced by specific particles and involves dropping the final vowel or weak letter."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "لَمْ: negates past (لَمْ يَذْهَبْ - he did not go)",
        "لَمَّا: negates continuing past (لَمَّا يَأْتِ - he has not come yet)",
        "لَا: prohibition (لَا تَذْهَبْ - don't go)",
        "لِ: command for 3rd person (لِيَذْهَبْ - let him go)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "لَمْ يَكْتُبْ", "english": "He did not write" },
        { "arabic": "لَا تَحْزَنْ", "english": "Do not be sad" }
      ]
    }
